  "original_title": "IMF \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dba\u0ddd\u0da2\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dba\u0ddd \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dc4\u0db8\u0dd4 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "IMF representatives meet the President",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A preliminary round of discussions with the International Monetary Fund to provide solutions to the financial crisis facing Sri Lanka was held today (24) afternoon at the President's Office under the chairmanship of President Ranil Wickramasinghe.",
        "The current situation of the financial crisis that Sri Lanka is facing was discussed here. It was further decided to hold another discussion in this round of discussions on Friday 26th and to discuss technical level issues with the Central Bank officials in the future.",
        "Peter Bruber, Head of the International Monetary Fund's Negotiation Panel, Deputy Head Osairo Kosaiko, Mr. Tubagans, Permanent Representative of the International Monetary Fund in Sri Lanka, and Chief of Staff to the President and Senior Advisor to the President on National Security Sagala Ratnayake, President's Secretary Saman Ekanayake, Central Bank Governor Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe. Gentlemen and others were present on this occasion."
      ],
